  "response": "The national anthem of Bangladesh, \"Amar Shonar Bangla\" (My Golden Bengal), was written by the renowned Bengali poet **Rabindranath Tagore**. He composed the song in 1905 during the first Bengali partition movement. When Bangladesh gained independence in 1971, the first ten lines of the song were adopted as the national anthem. Tagore, who also wrote the national anthem of India (\"Jana Gana Mana\"), is a celebrated cultural icon in both Bangladesh and India.",
